Date: Sat, 12 Jun 1999 15:57:24 -0500
From: Dayton L. (Pat) Prouty D.V.M. <bandipur@pyramid3.net

Has it been established that it is a bacteria that has caused the black
drum kill in Virginia? If so, what is the bacteria?
What has been the recent information on _Pfiesteria piscicida_? I recall
that this dinoflagellate was first reported to be a bacterium. There were
reports of illness in fisherman as well as research workers working with
infected fish. Some workers were reported to have had CNS problems.
--
Dayton L. "Pat" Prouty, DVM
